    _stories.add(Story(
      titleEn: "The Magical Family Dinner",
      titleAm: "ድንቅ የቤተሰብ እራት",
      contentEn:
          "Every Friday in the Abebe family home, something magical happened. Grandmother Kidist prepared a feast that brought everyone together from miles around. Her injera was so perfectly spongy that children believed it had been blessed by angels. Her doro wat was so rich and flavorful that neighbors could smell it three houses away. But the true magic wasn't in the food itself—it was in what happened around the table. As family members arrived, all arguments were forgotten. Cousins who had quarreled all week suddenly remembered they were best friends. Uncle Yonas's stories grew more incredible with each telling, and no one minded. Little Tigist always asked to hear how her parents met, even though she knew the story by heart. When Grandmother Kidist rang the small brass bell, everyone hurried to wash their hands. They gathered around the table, where steam rose from the dishes like morning mist over mountains. Before eating, each person shared one good thing that happened that week. Even on the hardest weeks, everyone found something to share. \"In our family,\" Grandmother often said, \"we eat the food, but we feast on our stories and love.\" Years later, when family members moved far away for school or work, they would close their eyes on Friday evenings and swear they could smell Grandmother's doro wat, carrying her love across any distance.",
